casebody.data:
Crooks, Respondent, v. Milwaukee & M. Ins. Co., Appellant. Same v. American Cent. Ins. Co., Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, Third Department. September 25, 1891.) Two actions by George W. Crooks, one against the Milwaukee & Michigan Insurance Company, and the other against the American Central Insurance Company.

Argued before Learned, P. J., and Landon and Mayham, JJ.

Ho opinion. Each order affirmed, with $10 costs and printing disbursements.
